@node d0050
@toc p013-demo

@{b}
    Greenday
@{ub}

     Producer  : Artwork

     Coder     : Tron, Crash/Polka Brothers
     Graphician: Fiver/TRSI, Noogman
     Sounder   : Virgill

     Size      : 360K (#1) + 663K (#2) + 647K (#3); 1,6Mb (HD-version)
     System    : AGA, 2Mb ChipMem, HD (2,7Mb); FastMem recommended
     How2Handle: automatic Exit, WB

     Genre     : Multifile-Demo (HD) (3d)


     WhatIsIt? : Another nice demo which requires a harddrive. Some
                 excellent routines but unfortunately some not too 
                 good ones aswell. You may say that Artwork was
                 founded because of this demo. (Wizard)
		 The first production from the German crew Artwork. (Dire)
@endnode

@node d0051
@toc p013-demo

@{b}
    Roots V2.0
@{ub}

     Producer  : Sanity

     Coder     : Chaos, Mr.Pet
     Graphician: Cthulhlu, Cougar
     Sounder   : Jester
     Designer  : Chaos

     Size      : 860K
     System    : AGA, 2Mb ChipMem
     Remark    : updated version of Roots V1.0 (The Party 4)

     Genre     : Diskdemo


     WhatIsIt? : This demo is probably the most prefectly put-together
                 demo ever. To fit everything the show has to offer
                 onto *1* disk is somekind of a miracle. Also, the
                 main-theme by Jester is the best demotune I've ever
                 heard. A really speedy song which really makes the
                 demo *better*. The first version of this demo was
                 released at THE PARTY4. Due to some harddrive crashes
                 they had problems with making the demo complete. I
                 guess that this final version would have done better
                 in the democompetition at TheParty4. But why don't
                 they use AGA graphics when the demo requires a 68020 
                 anyway? (Wizard)
@endnode

