@node d0086
@toc p028-demo

@{b}
    Switchback
@{ub}

     Producer  : Rebels

     Coder     : Zulu & Grey
     Graphician: Tee Vaan, Kris, Slime; add-ones: Demon, Eracore, Grey, SRL
     Sounder   : Chromag, Vocal

     Size      : 660K (#1) + 859K (#2)
     System    : AGA, 2Mb ChipMem
     How2Handle: demo supports external diskdrives
     Remark    : two versions available: for MC68020 and MC68030

     Genre     : Diskdemo (2d)


     WhatIsIt? : Demo was originally no. 1 at Doom`s Day Party 1994,
                 but rules stated that the demo must work on a stan-
                 dard A1200 (demo supported MC68030, but worked on a
                 A1200 MC68020 too!). So Rebels got only two bottles
                 of wine instead of the  winning price - seems to be
                 that the party-organisers  had less money than they
                 had expected :)  (Dire)

                 The second generation of Rebels proves they are
                 worthy their name. One of the first really good
                 AGA-trackmos released. Includes a stunning end-
                 part where the attender is given a free roller-
                 coaster trip.  Excellent endmusic  but I  don't
                 like the main-theme at all. (Wizard)
@endnode

