     Genre     : Multifile-Demo (HD) (4d)


     WhatIsIt? : With an excellent piece of art, Razor 1911 brought
                 some of the lost  honour back to the swedish demo-
                 scene. Excellent code,  excellent music and decent
                 graphics is  what this demo  has to offer.  Really
                 nice to see Mantronix back for a guestplay!
                 (Wizard)
@endnode

@node d0274
@toc p057-demo

@{b}
    Que?
@{ub}

     Producer  : The Black Lotus (TBL)

     Coder     : Equalizer, Offa
     Graphician: ST, Scorpax, Tudor, Axm
     Sounder   : Lizardking/Razor 1911, Mantronix/Phenomena

     Size      : 494K (#1) + 605K (#2); 2500K (HD)
     System    : needed: AGA; recommended: MC68030 + 28Mhz
     How2Handle: Exit

     Genre     : Multifile-Demo (HD) (2d)


     WhatIsIt? : This demo is a pretty odd mix of really good parts and
                 some really bad. Especially the quality of the design
                 is really up and down throughout the whole demo. Second 
                 at the Party Remedy'95. (Wizard)

@endnode

@node d0275
@toc p057-demo

@{b}
    ISO
@{ub}

     Producer  : Scoopex

     Coder     : Ninja
     Graphician: Made
     Sounder   : Oxbow

     Size      : 818K (#1) + 799K (#2); 1602K (HD-version)
     System    : AGA; 2Mb FastMem recommended; HD-installable
     How2Handle: demo supports external diskdrives

     Genre     : Diskdemo (2d)


     WhatIsIt? : Just when  I started to  feel the time of the
                 trackdemos were over I got this surprise from
                 Scoopex.  A nice trackmo  on two disks with a
                 really  nice  introduction.  Made  proves his
                 place as  one of the  absolutely best  Amiga-
                 graphicians of 1995!      (Wizard)
@endnode

