@node d0481
@toc p091-demo

@{b}
    Mindflow
@{ub}

     Producer  : Stellar

     Coder     : Zuikki, Nose
     Graphician: Frankie
     Sounder   : Strobo

     Size      : 736K
     System    : AGA, 2Mb ChipMem, 2Mb FastMem
     How2Handle: automatic Exit

     Genre     : Filedemo


     WhatIsIt? : The masters of intros finally decided to
                 make a demo. The result is really impressive.
                 Some really nice routines taking advantage of
                 fastmem in a truely nice way. Unfortuantely 
                 the demo has a sudden end which I presume was
                 caused by the demo-deadline at Assembly'94?
                 (Wizard)
@endnode

@node d0482
@toc p091-demo

@{b}
    Breathtaker
@{ub}

     Producer  : Virtual Dreams & Fairlight (VD-FLT)

     Coder     : Alien
     Graphician: Jaco
     Sounder   : Alien

     Size      : 6033K (HD-version)
     System    : HD, AGA, 6Mb Ram
     How2Handle: The first part is executable with 2Mb ChipMem too.

     Genre     : Multifile-Demo (HD) (4d)


     WhatIsIt? : With this demo, Virtual Dreams introduced the
                 graphical-only type of demo. The whole demo is
                 based upon awesome raytraced animations. The
                 animations are also very professional made.
                 (Wizard)
@endnode

@node d0483
@toc p091-demo

@{b}
    Drool This
@{ub}

     Producer  : Parallax

     Coder     : Debug, Simply
     Graphician: Mistral, Legend, Warthog
     Sounder   : Yolk, Legend

     Size      : 2350K (HD-version)
     System    : 4Mb FastMem, AGA
     How2Handle: 4-disks version must be installed on HD; 6-disks
                 version should be run without startup-sequence
                 to qork properly; Exit

     Genre     : Multifile-Demo (HD) (6 disks)


     WhatIsIt? : Another masterpiece released at the Assembly'94. This
                 one is a really huge demo which really uses the
                 strength of your machine. It features some nice
                 routines like a doom-engine, voxel-landscape and a
                 city-flyaround. It is stated that there is a A4000
                 version released but I can't really confirm that
                 myself. Annoying is that the music ends abruptly
                 a couple of times. (Wizard)
@endnode

@node d0484
@toc p091-demo

@{b}
    Ilyad
@{ub}

     Producer  : Alcatraz

     Coder     : Hornet, Shagan/Asphyxia Design
     Graphician: PGCS, Cookie/Asphyxia Design
     Sounder   : Zoltar

     Size      : 746K (#1) + 763K (#2) + 763K (#3) + 724K (#4) + 10K (fix)
     System    : AGA, 2Mb ChipMem, 4Mb FastMem
     How2Handle: Exit
     Remark    : A4000-fix (V1.4, Size: 10K) was released on 25-Sep-94

     Genre     : Multifile-Demo (HD) (4 disks)


     WhatIsIt? : It is the first of a new breed of demos - large, pretty
                 and well put together. Impressive indeed.  (Kenji Irie)

                 First version released at the Assembly'94, but as far as
                 I can remember it wasn't shown in its full length. Maybe
                 they didn't manage to get it all together in time. Any-
                 way, this demo is really awesome with no doubt the most
                 smashing first-part EVER. The soundeffects by Zoltar is
                 totally awesome. All in all I think that this shows that
                 those guys, who also gave us "Odyssey" a couple of years
                 earlier, are among the alltime BEST demo-makers.
                 (Wizard)
@endnode

@node d0485
@toc p091-demo

@{b}
    CCCP
@{ub}

     Producer  : Juliet and Case

     Coder     : Juliet, Case
     Graphician: Juliet, Case
     Sounder   : Groo, Defaulter

     Size      : 553K
     System    : AGA, 2Mb ChipMem
     How2Handle: no Exit, Relo

     Genre     : Filedemo
@endnode

@node d0486
@toc p091-demo

@{b}
    Maximum Overdrive 2
@{ub}

     Producer  : Rage

     Coder     : Goose, Derek
     Graphician: Ozzie
     Sounder   : Fajser

     Size      : 2399K (HD-version)
     System    : AGA, 2Mb ChipMem, HD-installable

     Genre     : Diskdemo (3d)


     WhatIsIt? : One of the funniest demos ever made. Say what you
                 want about Rage's political aspects but they sure
                 know how  to  entertain.  The two  disk digitized
                 animation is  really amusing  with morphing  of a
                 Volvo into a Starwars ship. And the parody on the 
                 "State Of The Art"  demo is quite funny.  If I do
                 not rememeber  wrong I think  that only the anim-
                 part  of the  demo were  actually  shown  at  the
                 Assembly'94. Too bad as the "real" demo part have
                 quite high quality.  Doesn't support x-drives (In
                 an old fashioned way.. ;-))   (Wizard)
@endnode

