@node d0573
@toc p096-demo

@{b}
    Desert Dreams
@{ub}

     Producer  : Kefrens

     Coder     : Laxity, Zeus, Vention
     Graphician: Laxity, Airwalk, R.W.O., Blizzart
     Sounder   : Laxity
     Designer  : Laxity, Airwalk, Zeus

     Size      : 553K (#1) + 310K (#2)
     System    : 1Mb Ram, OCS
     SecretPart: There are actually two hidden-parts.Boot Disk 2 and press
                 both mousebottons+joystick to reach the hidden-part. After
                 a while, when the line-effects are over you can see
                 the 2nd hidden-part...
     How2Handle: Exit, KillAga; demo supports external diskdrives

     Genre     : Diskdemo (2d)


     WhatIsIt? : This demo is something which could be called
                 a one-man-power-hit. Laxity shows his talents
                 on all fields of demo designing. (Dire)

                 If you can give a demo the title "classic", this
                 is definately a worthy contender to this title. 
                 It is also a flash of the REAL past as most of
                 the producers behind this demo had been in the
                 *old* Kefrens. All in all this demo was the un-
                 discussable number one when it was released. Of
                 course it took the first place at TG '93. Nice 
                 introduction with somekind of "joke" towards 
                 Melon Dezign (I guess..). (Wizard)
@endnode

