@node d0667
@toc p099-demo

@{b}
    Odyssey
@{ub}

     Producer  : Alcatraz

     Coder     : Hornet
     Graphician: PGCS
     Sounder   : Greg, Zoltar, Moby?

     Size      : 2 * 5 * 451K (for #1a+b, #2a+b, #3a+b, #4a+b, #5a+b);
                 748K (HD-Installer), 115K (Patch); or HD-version: 3363K
     System    : HD-installable, some problems with AGA-machines may occur
     How2Handle: Relo; A500-owners with no FastMem but much ChipMem
                 use the Patch (Chip2Fast.exe); demo supports external 
                 diskdrives
     Remark    : running time: over 40 minutes!

     Genre     : Diskdemo (5d)


     WhatIsIt? : This classic demo invites us to a real space-odyssey.
                 It got a lot of critics because many other coders
                 found the demo "too easy to code". I guess it was the
                 good old jealousy who made them say so about this
                 demo. Maybe it is easy to code but it sure is nice
                 to watch. (Wizard)

                 1991? Odyssey? ASTONISHING! (Dire)
@endnode

@node d0668
@toc p099-demo

@{b}
    Hardwired
@{ub}

     Producer  : The Silents, Crionics

     Coder     : The Spy, Deftronic, Murphy, Saxs, Guzzler
     Graphician: Mikael Balle, Sionic, Zycho
     Sounder   : Jesper Kyd

     Size      : 590K (#1) + 698K (#2); 1318K (HD-version)
     System    : 1Mb Ram, OCS, not compatible with A3000; HD-installable

     Genre     : Diskdemo (2d)


     WhatIsIt? : One of the most glory groups EVER with their
                 masterpiece of the old days. HardWired became
                 the number one on the charts for a very long
                 time. This demo was also somekind of a goodbye
                 to the Amiga-scene from Mikael Balle and Jesper
                 Kyd, two of the most famous scene-individuals 
                 of all time. (Wizard)
@endnode

