@node d0742
@toc p101-demo

@{b}
    Origin
@{ub}

     Producer  : Complex

     Coder     : Gengis
     Graphician: Titan, Hof, Mack, Alex
     Sounder   : Clawz

     Size      : 867K (#1) + 822K (#2)
     System    : AGA, 2Mb ChipMem
     How2Handle: do a safety-copy because the demo sometimes
                 doesn`t work anymore after the first run

     Genre     : Diskdemo (2d)


     WhatIsIt? : All in all a very nice demo with an excellent
                 introduction. Four good graphicians don't make 
                 this worse. (Wizard)
@endnode

@node d0743
@toc p101-demo

@{b}
    Full Moon
@{ub}

     Producer  : Virtual Dreams & Fairlight (VD-FLT)

     Coder     : Dr. Skull
     Graphician: Jaco, Alien, Kerberos
     Sounder   : Jogeir, Heatbeat

     Size      : 801K
     System    : AGA, 2Mb ChipMem, HD-installable
     How2Handle: Exit, WB

     Genre     : Filedemo


     WhatIsIt? : This is a demo which just about can be put on
                 one single DD Disk. It is a really well-executed
                 production with excellent music by Heatbeat and
                 Jogeir Liljedahl. Somekind of a breakthrough from  
                 the people behind the label Virtual Dreams.
                 (Wizard)
@endnode

@node d0744
@toc p101-demo

@{b}
    Arte
@{ub}

     Producer  : Sanity

     Coder     : Mr. Pet, Chaos, McDeal
     Graphician: Ra
     Sounder   : Moby

     Size      : 813K
     System    : 1Mb Ram, OCS
     How2Handle: turbo card speeds up the demo

     Genre     : Diskdemo


     WhatIsIt? : Sanity's first attempt to smash incredible amounts
                 of data onto one single disk. It is a really nice 
                 demo which really brought the good old A500 to its 
                 outer limits. Really nice music, this time by Moby.
                 (Wizard)
@endnode

@node d0745
@toc p101-demo

@{b}
    9 Fingers
@{ub}

     Producer  : Spaceballs

     Coder     : Lone Starr
     Sounder   : Travolta

     Size      : 1644K (HD-version); 819K (#1) + 825K (#2)
     System    : HD-installable, OCS, 0,5Mb ChipMem, 0,5Mb FastMem
     How2Handle: demo supports external diskdrives

     Genre     : Diskdemo (2d)


     WhatIsIt? : A follow-up to the popular State Of Art - demo.
                 I think that this is the most ENTERTAINING demo
                 ever made. Many other coders didn't like this
                 demo as they found it too easy to code. Still,
                 there haven't been any similiar demos relased!
                 (Or at least none of them have been even close
                 to this one) One of few demos which you can show
                 for people not usually interested in the world
                 of computers. This also became the last demo 
                 from Lone Starr. (Wizard)
@endnode

