@node d0801
@toc p102-demo

@{b}
    Nexus 7
@{ub}

     Producer  : Andromeda

     Coder     : Dr.Jekyll, Mr.Hyde
     Graphician: Archmage
     Sounder   : Interphace
     Designer  : View

     Size      : 782K
     System    : AGA, 2Mb ChipMem, HD-installable
     How2Handle: Exit, WB

     Genre     : Filedemo


     WhatIsIt? : This sort of demo is what the Amiga was made for: bril-
                 liant smooth graphics &  impressive effects  & sound to
                 match. Amazing it all fits onto less than a disk.  Even
                 though released in 94,  it`s a demo any Amigan would be
                 proud to have. Excellent even on a standard 1200.
                 (Kenji Irie)

                 Nexus 7 is great! (Zerox/Iris in DISC 10)

                 A classic! Watch it now! (Dr.Dreyer)
@endnode

@node d0802
@toc p102-demo

@{b}
    Psychedelic
@{ub}

     Producer  : Virtual Dreams & Fairlight (VD-FLT)

     Coder     : Dr. Skull
     Graphician: Ra, Alien
     Sounder   : Probe, Julius/Polka Brothers, Excellate

     Size      : 765K (#1) + 713K (#2) + 602K (#3); 2130K (HD)
     System    : AGA, 2Mb ChipMem, 4Mb FastMem, HD
     How2Handle: Exit, WB

     Genre     : Multifile-Demo (HD) (3d)


     WhatIsIt? : Another amazing demonstration from the finnish
                 group Virtual Dreams. This time they really try
                 to aim high by putting in hundreds of different
                 routines. Unfortunately it ends up with an
                 average design. A very annoying fact is that the
                 first music stops abruptly. This could of course
                 have been forced by the demo-deadline at TheParty4.
                 Overall it is still an impressing demo with really 
                 good *coding*. (But, where are the credits??)
                 (Wizard)
@endnode

@node d0803
@toc p102-demo

@{b}
    Motion - Origin 2
@{ub}

     Producer  : Bomb!

     Coder     : Gengis, Made
     Graphician: Suny, Trajan, Zebig, Hof
     Sounder   : Clawz

     Size      : 801K (#1) + 383K (#2); 1183K (HD-version)
     System    : AGA, 2Mb ChipMem, HD-installable
     How2Handle: Exit, WB

     Genre     : Diskdemo (2d)


     WhatIsIt? : One of the best coders ever once again proved he
                 should be on top. This demo is a sequel to the 
                 winning demo at TheParty3 (Complex, Origin). I
                 really like the way Gengis is handling vectors
                 and texturemapped stuff. He seems to be a really 
                 mathematic kind of person!? This demo finished
                 number two on TheParty4 and I guess it was the
                 DOOM-clone part that really set the voters on
                 fire. Later on they have also released a DOOM
                 type-of game called Fears. Go and buy it and do 
                 these fellows a favour! (Wizard)
@endnode

@node d0804
@toc p102-demo

@{b}
    Soul Kitchen
@{ub}

     Producer  : The Silents

     Coder     : Crush, Ricky
     Graphician: Dize
     Sounder   : Scortia

     Size      : 1642K (HD-version)
     System    : AGA, 2Mb ChipMem, HD-installable

     Genre     : Diskdemo (2d)


     WhatIsIt? : The second generation of Silents Denmark
                 decided to bring back some of the lost Silents
                 glory. This demo maybe isn't any success but
                 although I think it proves that Silents still
                 is to be counted on. Nice introduction-animation! 
                 Followups in the "kitchen" series promised. Has
                 this "kitchen" stuff anything to do with Anarchys
                 old demo named "In The Kitchen"? (Wizard)
@endnode

@node d0805
@toc p102-demo

@{b}
    Whammer Slammer
@{ub}

     Producer  : Rebels

     Coder     : Zulu & Grey, Newton
     Graphician: Teevaan, Eracore, Slime, Cueball
     Sounder   : Chromag, Vocal
     Designer  : Zulu, Grey, Excess

     Size      : 2040K (HD-version)
     System    : AGA, 2Mb ChipMem, HD-installable
     How2Handle: uses external diskdrive

     Genre     : Diskdemo (3d)


     WhatIsIt? : Really ordinary stuff lead to an honourable fifth
                 spot at The Party 4.  Nice graphics  as always by
                 Teewaan.  But  where  is the load  while  playing
                 when running from disk? (Wizard)
@endnode

@node d0806
@toc p102-demo

@{b}
    The Prey
@{ub}

     Producer  : Polka Brothers

     Coder     : Merge, Airwalk, Slide
     Graphician: Pixie, Devilstar/VD-FLT
     Sounder   : Slide, Colin, Vandrup

     Size      : 534K (#1) + 551K (#2)
     System    : AGA, 2Mb ChipMem, HD-installable (1,4Mb)
     How2Handle: Exit, WB

     Genre     : Diskdemo (2d)


     WhatIsIt? : When I first watched this demo it was kind of a
                 disappointment. I had expected Polka Brothers to 
                 smash all opponents into pieces at The Party 4.
                 Although, this is of course not a bad demo. I just
                 expected too much ... (Wizard)
@endnode

