@node d1223
@toc p141-a1200demo

@{b}
    Tint
@{ub}

     Producer  : The Black Lotus

     Coder     : Offa, Equalizer
     Graphician: Danny, Facet, Louie, Rodney
     Sounder   : Azazel
     Designer  : Tudor

     Size      : 884K (#1) + 889K (#2) + 885K (#3) +
                 877K (#4) + 885K (#5) + 430K (#6); 4767K (HD-version)
     System    : AGA; 4Mb FastMem; 68030/28MHz recommended; HD-installable
     How2Handle: 040-patch for 68040-owners

     Genre     : Diskdemo (6d)


     WhatIsIt? : This demo  has set the  standard for  forthcoming  demo
                 releases. Professionally presented,  this demo achieves
                 near  perfection  in all parts,  and  flows  exquisitly
                 between sections.  The demo is presented almost entire-
                 ly in 2x2 pixel mode,   but do not  let this fool you -
                 Bumpmapped  lightsourced  objects  look brilliant.  The
                 demo  contains a lot of  3d  object manipulations,  and
                 amazing tunnel sequences,  and has a brilliant thumping
                 and atmospheric soundtrack to go with it. (Kenji Irie)

                 Almost everything! (Dr.Dreyer)

                 Even two of my friends, proud (?) owners of PC`s and 
                 Atari Falcon`s, were impressed!  (Dire)
@endnode

